Basic Commands in Linux:

ls --> list files and directories

ls -l --> list files and directories in long listing format

ls -a --> list files and directories with hidden files & directories

ls -la --> list all files and directories including hidden files and directory

ls -i --> list files and directories with index number and inode number

ls -lr --> list files and directories with reverse order

ls -lrt --> list files and directories with long listing, reverse order and modification time

ls -lrth --> list files and directories with long listing, reverse order, modification time and human readable format.
